CLIPBOARD; 
HAZARDOUS SPILLS LOG 
The Orange County Hazardous Materials Team, administered by the county Health 
Care Agency's division of environmental health, responds to calls on chemical 
spills and other incidents involving hazardous materials. Sometimes the team 
goes to the site and other times it advises citizens or local fire departments 
over the phone. 
There were 29 spills recorded in HAZMAT's response logs in September. The 
following details the seven spills that occurred in the Costa Mesa/Newport 
Beach/Irvine area of the county. 
Date: Sept. 6 
Location of Incident: 592 Superior Ave., Newport Beach 
Material Handler: City of Newport Beach 
Materials Involved: Unknown 
Date: Sept. 8 
Location of Incident: 3450 Via Oporto, Newport Beach 
Material Handler: Newport Harbor Yacht Club 
Materials Involved: Oil and water mixture 
Date: Sept. 15 
Location of Incident: 2806 Lafayette Ave., Newport Beach 
Material Handler: U.S. Coast Guard 
Materials Involved: Diesel fuel 
Date: Sept. 16 
Location of Incident: 14417 Culver Drive, Irvine 
Material Handler: City of Irvine 
Materials Involved: Unknown 
Date: Sept. 17 
Location of Incident: 18321 Jamboree Road, Irvine 
Material Handler: Parker-Hannifin 
Materials Involved: Adhesive containing strontium chromate 
Date: Sept. 17 
Location of Incident: 17150 Von Karman Ave., Irvine 
Material Handler: Hughes Aircraft 
Materials Involved: Hydrochloric acid 
Date: Sept. 25 
Location of Incident: 3333 Michelson Drive, Irvine 
Material Handler: Fluor Corp. 
Materials Involved: Ammonia 
HAZARDOUS SPILLS REPORTED IN THE COSTA MESA/NEWPORT BEACH/IRVINE AREA 
